      <h1>International Comparison</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">How the US 3PPS system contrasts with Third-Party Observation mechanisms in other major patent jurisdictions.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout tldr"><span class="callout-label">TL;DR</span><p>The US 3PPS (sometimes called a "US Third-Party Observation" internationally) is the most restrictive system — facts only, brittle timing, and a small fee. The EPO and PCT allow legal arguments and are free. Consider parallel filings in multiple jurisdictions.</p></div>

